<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Your OTP Code</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        text-align: center;
        background-color: #f4f4f4;
        padding: 20px;
      }
      .email-container {
        background: white;
        width: 400px;
        margin: auto;
        border-radius: 8px;
        box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
      }
      .header {
        background: #5a4fcf;
        color: white;
        padding: 15px;
        font-size: 18px;
        font-weight: bold;
      }
      .content {
        padding: 20px;
        font-size: 16px;
        color: #333;
      }
      .otp-box {
        display: inline-block;
        background: #f4f4f4;
        padding: 10px;
        font-size: 24px;
        font-weight: bold;
        letter-spacing: 2px;
        border-radius: 5px;
        margin: 10px 0;
      }
      .footer {
        font-size: 12px;
        color: #777;
        padding: 10px;
        background: #f4f4f4;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="email-container">
      <div class="header">Your OTP Code</div>
      <div class="content">
        <p>Hello,</p>
        <p>Your One-Time Password (OTP) for account verification is:</p>
        <div class="otp-box"><%= otp %></div>
        <p>
          This OTP is valid for <b>2 minutes</b>. Please do not share this code
          with anyone.
        </p>
        <p>If you didn't request this code, please ignore this email.</p>
        <p>Thank you for using our service!</p>
      </div>
      <div class="footer">
        &copy; 2024 Your Company Name. All rights reserved.
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
